138
00:21:33,954 --> 00:21:42,178
[SPEAKER_02]: So it's costly for investment, and I would say that it is cheaper to produce in Africa.

139
00:21:42,539 --> 00:21:51,263
[SPEAKER_02]: So you create wealth, you create jobs for youth, you reduce the carbon footprint, you just win-win for social, environmental, and economic gains.

140
00:21:52,024 --> 00:21:59,908
[SPEAKER_02]: But again, because of path dependency, that would change except if African countries make the policies to change it.

